modules.description: Provides functions to read user input with line editing, manage input history, and persist it to a file. Works with strings and maintains a history of previously entered commands. Used to create interactive command-line applications that remember past inputs and allow editing during entry.

Initializes a readline session with customizable history handling, prompt, and signal behavior. Reads user input with optional tab completion based on filenames, usernames, or custom lists, and supports modifying history entries. Adjusts word break characters for custom completion logic.
